.TH "zpa2326_set_trigger_state" 9 "zpa2326_set_trigger_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zpa2326_set_trigger_state \- Start / stop continuous sampling.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zpa2326_set_trigger_state
.BI "(struct iio_trigger *trig "  ","
.BI "bool state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "trig" 12
The trigger being attached to IIO device associated with the sampling
hardware.
.IP "state" 12
Tell whether to start (true) or stop (false)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Basically enable / disable hardware continuous sampling mode.

Called with IIO device's lock held at \fBpostenable\fP or \fBpredisable\fP time.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero when successful, a negative error code otherwise.
